{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T06:08:47.233192587Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-ee57a8b1","body":"The acceptance criterion states: 'Output from task commands explains the task↔project mapping where useful (e.g., Task foo (project foo))'. Currently task commands delegate directly to project::handle() which prints project-oriented messages (e.g., 'Selected project {id}'). The task handler should intercept at least the select/show/create output paths to add task-aware messaging, or the acceptance criterion should be explicitly relaxed.","dedup_key":"ab5d57278ee27e19d5f7404eb2f7ffb024da145fe0a0e6cbefffb71825c656f0","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260409055104","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T06:08:47.241913921Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-df1751ba","body":"In src/cli/task.rs test task_create_maps_to_project_create_from_bead_args (line 209), the assertion set checks milestone_id, bead_id, project_id, and flow but omits prompt_file. Add `assert_eq!(task_args.prompt_file, project_args.prompt_file);` for completeness.","dedup_key":"f91c2765ecbbcc277973f3a0f312f2600a52e5b57c43ae9ac19f71f2a17c4aa3","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260409055104","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T06:08:47.250439628Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-f7e2dae5","body":"Make the `task` namespace render task-aware output and remediation text instead of forwarding directly to `project::handle`. Right now `src/cli/task.rs:52-83` delegates every subcommand unchanged, so `task select`, `task list`, `task show`, and `task create` inherit project-only strings from `src/cli/project.rs:154-159`, `src/cli/project.rs:578-607`, `src/cli/project.rs:506-508`, `src/cli/project.rs:665-675`, and `src/cli/project.rs:1993-1999`, plus project-only fallback errors from `src/shared/error.rs:38-47`. On this branch, `ralph-burning task show 9ni92` prints `Project: 9ni92 (active)` and `ralph-burning task select 9ni92` prints `Selected project 9ni92`, so the new command surface does not actually explain the task<->project mapping or keep users in task vocabulary.","dedup_key":"e62a90e845ac3d8231c9aedf319cecaf70f5f6206c623780a0ef75dd4c55c5a4","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409055104","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T06:08:47.259082585Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-0f05076d","body":"Add deterministic behavioral tests for the new `task` namespace. The only new coverage is the parser-focused unit tests in `src/cli/task.rs:95-272`, and the strongest equivalence check in `src/cli/task.rs:206-257` only compares parsed argument structs. There is no end-to-end CLI coverage proving that `task create/show/select/list` execute the same behavior as their project counterparts or that the task-facing output stays correct. Add integration tests that run both namespaces against a temp workspace and compare resulting state/output, especially for `task create` and the no-active-project path.","dedup_key":"82fe0c72f4cfa58fbb68e6656f75327c953d582114b42b38857028125922e184","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409055104","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
